Communication and concurrency
-----------------------------

Warning: this folder may be updated and replaced by a new version on Canvas.

We have the following subfolders with teaching examples:

0-introduction

  This is a demo, which contains everything we'll see in this topic,
  and which I will run in the first lecture.

1-threads

  https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thread_%28computing%29
  https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/concurrency/threads.html
  
2-races

  https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Race_condition
  https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/concurrency/sync.html

3-deadlocks

  https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deadlock
  https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/concurrency/deadlock.html

4-sockets

  Client-server systems using sockets
  https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Client%E2%80%93server_model
  https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/networking/sockets/
  
5-serialization-pitfalls
